Section 1:
1 L.D. 1934
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 1295,
9 L.D. 1934, “An Act to Promote Responsible Outdoor Lighting”
10 Amend the amendment in paragraph E in the 3rd line (page 1, line 20 in amendment)
11 by inserting after the following: "708" the following: ', Maine Turnpike Authority roadway
12 lighting'
13 Amend the amendment by inserting after paragraph A the following:
14 'Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 21 in §481 in subsection 3 by inserting after paragraph
15 D the following:
16 'E. Rules adopted pursuant to subsection 4 by the Maine Turnpike Authority permit
17 temporary lighting to ensure safety and efficiency in completion of road construction
18 and repair, as long as such lighting deviates from the standards in subsection 2 to the
19 minimum extent necessary;' '
20 Amend the amendment on page 2 by inserting after paragraph H the following:
21 'Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 21 in §481 in subsection 3 by relettering the
22 paragraphs to read alphabetically.'
23 Amend the amendment on page 2 in subsection 4 in the 6th and 7th lines (page 2, lines
24 11 and 12 in amendment) by striking out the following: "Any department proposing rules"
25 and inserting the following: 'The Maine Turnpike Authority may adopt rules governing
26 temporary lighting necessary to ensure safety and efficiency in completion of road
27 construction and repair as described in subsection 3, paragraph E. Any entity proposing
28 rules pursuant to this subsection'
29 Amend the amendment on page 2 in subsection 5 in the 3rd and 4th lines (page 2, lines
30 19 and 20 in amendment) by striking out the following: "No later than September 30, 2026,
31 the" and inserting the following: 'The'
32 Amend the amendment on page 2 in subsection 5 in the first paragraph in the last line
33 (page 2, line 21 in amendment) by inserting after the following: "purposes" the following:
34 'when the office has sufficient resources to accomplish this'
35 Amend the amendment on page 2 by striking out all of the 3rd instructional paragraph
36 (page 2, line 26 in amendment).
Page 1 - 132LR1969(05)
SENATE AMENDMENT
SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 1295, L.D. 1934
1 Amend the amendment on page 2 by striking out all of section 2 (page 2, lines 27 to 36
2 in amendment).
3 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
4 section number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment removes the requirement that the Maine Office of Community Affairs
77 develop and share with municipalities a model ordinance for lighting standards by
88 September 30, 2026. Instead, the amendment specifies that the office must accomplish this
99 requirement when it has sufficient resources. The amendment also exempts roadway
1100 lighting on the Maine Turnpike and provides to the Maine Turnpike Authority the authority
1111 to adopt major substantive rules to exempt temporary lighting to ensure safety and
1122 efficiency in completion of road construction and repair, as long as such lighting deviates
1133 from the standards to the minimum extent necessary. The amendment also removes the
1144 appropriations and allocations section.
1155 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
1166 (Senator BALDACCI, J.)
1177 COUNTY: Penobscot
Page 2 - 132LR1969(05)
SENATE AMENDMENT
